      "title": "[New Atlas] Google spinoff beams blazing-fast internet around cities using light",
      "content_html": "<img src=\"https://assets.newatlas.com/dims4/default/93bf8d9/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1200x630+0+85/resize/1200x630!/quality/90/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fnewatlas-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd6%2F47%2Fb61cf06a4a53827971c97568f4d4%2Fthe-taara-beam-shoots-data-at-25gbps-between-pole-mounted-units-using-beams-of-light.jpg&na.image_optimisation=0\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<p><img alt=\"The Taara Beam shoots data at 25Gbps between pole-mounted units using beams of light\" src=\"https://assets.newatlas.com/dims4/default/220ab3d/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1200x800+0+0/resize/1200x800!/format/webp/quality/90/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fnewatlas-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd6%2F47%2Fb61cf06a4a53827971c97568f4d4%2Fthe-taara-beam-shoots-data-at-25gbps-between-pole-mounted-units-using-beams-of-light.jpg\" /><p>Over the last few years, an ambitious moonshot project spun out of Google has been developing fascinating technologies to deliver connectivity across communities without the need for underground cables. For its latest trick, Taara is now providing high-speed internet access across cities using invisible beams of light.</p><p><a href=\"https://newatlas.com/telecommunications/google-taara-25gbps-internet-cities-light/\">Continue Reading</a></p><p><b>Category:</b> <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/telecommunications/\">Telecommunications</a>, <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/technology/\">Technology</a></p><p><b>Tags:</b> <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/tag/taara/\" rel=\"tag\">Taara</a>, <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/tag/alphabet/\" rel=\"tag\">Alphabet</a>, <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/tag/fiber-optics/\" rel=\"tag\">Fiber optics</a>, <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/tag/internet/\" rel=\"tag\">Internet</a>, <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/tag/broadband/\" rel=\"tag\">Broadband</a></p>",
